n, m, p = [int(x) for x in input().split()]
    a = [int(x) for x in input().split()]
    b = [int(x) for x in input().split()]
    a.sort()
    b.sort()
    count = 0
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(m):
            if a[i] + p*j == b[j]:
                count += 1
    print(count)
    for i in range(count):
        print(b[i], end=" ")
